HEADWORD: Contrafissure
<hw>Con`tra*fis"sure</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A fissure or fracture on the side opposite to
that which received the blow, or at some distance from it.</def>
<rj><qau>Coxe.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Contrahent</ent>⟦br⟧
